Rook.java
3   public class Rook extends ChessPiece {
4  
5       public boolean hasMoved;
6  
7       public Rook(String color, String image) {
8           super(color, image);
9       }
10  
11       public boolean verify_move(int[][] board, int[] position, int[] next) {
12  
13           if (!canDefeat(color, board[next[0]][next[1]])) {
14               return false;
15           }
16  
17           int RowDiff = next[0] - position[0];
18           int ColDiff = next[1] - position[1];
19  
20           int RowIncr = 0;
21           int ColIncr = 0;
22           boolean validVector = false;
23  
24           //going up/down
25           if (ColDiff == 0) {
26               if (RowDiff > 0) {
27                   RowIncr = 1;
28                   ColIncr = 0;
29               } else {
30                   RowIncr = -1;
31                   ColIncr = 0;
32               }
33               validVector = true;
34           }
35           //going left/right
36           if (RowDiff == 0) {
37               if (ColDiff > 0) {
38                   RowIncr = 0;
39                   ColIncr = 1;
40               } else {
41                   RowIncr = 0;
42                   ColIncr = -1;
43               }
44               validVector = true;
45           }
46  
47           if (validVector) {
48               int testRow = position[0] + RowIncr;
49               int testCol = position[1] + ColIncr;
50               while (!(testRow == next[0] && testCol == next[1]) && board[testRow][testCol] == 0) {
51                   testRow = testRow + RowIncr;
52                   testCol = testCol + ColIncr;
53               }
54               if (testRow == next[0] && testCol == next[1]) {
55                   hasMoved = true;
56               }
57               return true;
58           }
59           return false;
60       }
61   }

20           boolean RookVector = false;
21           boolean BishopVector = false;
22  
23           //going up/down
24           if (ColDiff == 0) {
25               if (RowDiff > 0) {

27                   ColIncr = 0;
28               } else {

35           if (RowDiff == 0) {
36               if (ColDiff > 0) {

66               int testRow = position[0] + RowIncr;

70                   testCol = testCol + ColIncr;
71               }

3   public class King extends ChessPiece {
4  
5       public King(String color, String image) {
6           super(color, image);
7       }
8  
9       public boolean verify_move(int[][] board, int[] position, int[] next) {
10  
11           if (!canDefeat(color, board[next[0]][next[1]])) {
12               return false;
13           }
14  
15           int RowDiff = next[0] - position[0];
16           int ColDiff = next[1] - position[1];
17           if (Math.abs(RowDiff) > 1 || Math.abs(ColDiff) > 1) {
18               return false;
19           }
20  
21           if (isThereCheck(board, next)) {
22               return false;
23           }
24  
25           hasMoved = true;
26           return true;
27       }
28  
29       public boolean isThereCheck(int[][] board, int[] target) {
30  
31           int myKing = 1;
32           int enemyKing = 8;
33           int enemyQueen = 9;
34           int enemyRook1 = 10;
35           int enemyRook2 = 11;
36           int enemyKnight = 12;
37           int enemyBishop = 13;
38           int enemyPawn = 14;
39  
40           if (color.equals("black")) {
41               myKing = 8;
42               enemyKing = 1;
43               enemyQueen = 2;
44               enemyRook1 = 3;
45               enemyRook2 = 4;
46               enemyKnight = 5;
47               enemyBishop = 6;
48               enemyPawn = 7;
49           }
50  
51           int row = target[0];
52           int column = target[1];
53  
54           //evaluating threat from a Rook or Queen
55           int[][] RVectors = new int[][]{{1, 0}, {-1, 0}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}};
56  
57           for (int i = 0; i < RVectors.length; i++) {
58               int testRow = row + RVectors[i][0];
59               int testCol = column + RVectors[i][1];
60               while (validSquare(new int[]{testRow, testCol}) && (board[testRow][testCol] == 0 || board[testRow][testCol] == myKing)) {
61                   testRow = testRow + RVectors[i][0];
62                   testCol = testCol + RVectors[i][1];
63               }
64               if (validSquare(new int[]{testRow, testCol})) {
65                   if (board[testRow][testCol] == enemyRook1 || board[testRow][testCol] == enemyRook2 || board[testRow][testCol] == enemyQueen) {
66                       return true;
67                   }
68               }
69           }
70  
71           //evaluating threat from a Bishop or Queen
72           int[][] BVectors = new int[][]{{1, 1}, {1, -1}, {-1, 1}, {-1, -1}};
73  
74           for (int i = 0; i < BVectors.length; i++) {
75               int testRow = row + BVectors[i][0];
76               int testCol = column + BVectors[i][1];
77               while (validSquare(new int[]{testRow, testCol}) && (board[testRow][testCol] == 0 || board[testRow][testCol] == myKing)) {
78                   testRow = testRow + BVectors[i][0];
79                   testCol = testCol + BVectors[i][1];
80               }
81               if (validSquare(new int[]{testRow, testCol})) {
82                   if (board[testRow][testCol] == enemyBishop || board[testRow][testCol] == enemyQueen) {
83                       return true;
84                   }
85               }
86           }
87  
88           //evaluating threat from a Knight
89           int[][] Kvectors = new int[][]{{1, 2}, {1, -2}, {-1, 2}, {-1, -2}, {2, 1}, {2, -1}, {-2, 1}, {-2, -1}};
90  
91           for (int i = 0; i < Kvectors.length; i++) {
92               int[] move = {Kvectors[i][0] + row, Kvectors[i][1] + column};
93               if (validSquare(move) && board[move[0]][move[1]] == enemyKnight) {
94                   return true;
95               }
96           }
97  
98           //evaluating threat from a Pawn
99           int[][] pawnThreats;
100           if (color.equals("white")) {
101               pawnThreats = new int[][]{{-1, 1}, {-1, -1}};
102           } else {
103               pawnThreats = new int[][]{{1, 1}, {1, -1}};
104           }
105  
106           for (int i = 0; i < pawnThreats.length; i++) {
107               int[] move = {pawnThreats[i][0] + row, pawnThreats[i][1] + column};
108               if (validSquare(move) && board[move[0]][move[1]] == enemyPawn) {
109                   return true;
110               }
111           }
112  
113           //evaluating threat from a King
114           int[][] directions = new int[][]{{1, 0}, {1, 1}, {1, -1}, {-1, 0}, {-1, 1}, {-1, -1}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}};
115  
116           for (int i = 0; i < directions.length; i++) {
117               int[] move = {directions[i][0] + row, directions[i][1] + column};
118               if (validSquare(move) && board[move[0]][move[1]] == enemyKing) {
119                   return true;
120               }
121           }
122  
123           return false;
124  
125       }
126  
127       public boolean isThereCheckMate(int[][] board, int[] position) {
128  
129           int[][] directions = new int[][]{{1, 0}, {1, 1}, {1, -1}, {-1, 0}, {-1, 1}, {-1, -1}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}};
130  
131           for (int i = 0; i < directions.length; i++) {
132               int[] move = {directions[i][0] + position[0], directions[i][1] + position[1]};
133               if (validSquare(move) && canDefeat(color, board[move[0]][move[1]]) && !isThereCheck(board, move)) {
134                   return false;
135               }
136           }
137           //exited for-loop, means every possible move is under check
138           return true;
139       }

142           if (position[0] >= 0 && position[0] <= 7) {
143               if (position[1] >= 0 && position[1] <= 7) {
144                   return true;
145               }
146           }
147           return false;
148       }

Bishop.java
3   public class Bishop extends ChessPiece {
4  
5       public Bishop(String color, String image) {
6           super(color, image);
7       }
8  
9       public boolean verify_move(int[][] board, int[] position, int[] next) {
10  
11           if (!canDefeat(color, board[next[0]][next[1]])) {
12               return false;
13           }
14  
15           int RowDiff = next[0] - position[0];
16           int ColDiff = next[1] - position[1];
17  
18           if (RowDiff == 0 || ColDiff == 0) {
19               return false;
20           }
21           if (Math.abs(RowDiff / ColDiff) != 1) {
22               return false;
23           }
24  
25           int RowIncr;
26           int ColIncr;
27  
28           if (RowDiff > 0) {
29               RowIncr = 1;
30           } else {
31               RowIncr = -1;
32           }
33  
34           if (ColDiff > 0) {
35               ColIncr = 1;
36           } else {
37               ColIncr = -1;
38           }
39  
40           int testRow = position[0] + RowIncr;
41           int testCol = position[1] + ColIncr;
42           while (!(testRow == next[0] && testCol == next[1]) && board[testRow][testCol] == 0) {
43               testRow = testRow + RowIncr;
44               testCol = testCol + ColIncr;
45           }
46           if (testRow == next[0] && testCol == next[1]) {
47               return true;
48           }
49  
50           return false;
51  
52       }
53   }

83           public void applyMove(int[] current, int[] next){
84               
85               int pieceID = board[current[0]][current[1]];
86               
87               // Special Move: En Passant
88               if (pieceID == 7 || pieceID == 14){
89                   if (current[1] != next[1] && board[next[0]][next[1]] == 0){
90                       board[current[0]][next[1]] = 0;
91                   }
92               }
93               
94               // Special Move: Castling
95               if ((pieceID == 1 || pieceID == 8 ) && Math.abs(current[1] - next[1]) == 2){
96                   // White King, Queenside castling
97                   if (pieceID == 1 && next[1] == 2){
98                       board[7][3] = 3;
99                       board[7][0] = 0;
100                   }
101                   // White King, Kingside castling
102                   if (pieceID == 1 && next[1] == 6){
103                       board[7][5] = 4;
104                       board[7][7] = 0;
105                   }
106                   // Black King, Queenside castling
107                   if (pieceID == 8 & next[1] == 2){
108                       board[0][3] = 10;
109                       board[0][0] = 0;
110                   }
111                   // Black King, Kingside castling
112                   if (pieceID == 8 && next[1] == 6){
113                       board[0][5] = 11;
114                       board[0][7] = 0;
115                   }
116               }
117               
118               // Common for all moves
119               board[next[0]][next[1]] = pieceID;
120               board[current[0]][current[1]] = 0;
121               lastMove[0] = current;
122               lastMove[1] = next;
123               
124               // Promotion
125               if(pieceID == 7 && next[0] == 0)
126                   board[next[0]][next[1]] = 2;
127               if(pieceID == 14 && next[0] == 7)
128                   board[next[0]][next[1]] = 9;        
129               
130               // Set King Position
131               if(pieceID == 1)
132                   WKingPos = next;                
133               if(pieceID == 8)
134                   BKingPos = next;                
135               
136               // Set hasMoved Boolean for King or Rook
137               if (pieceID == 1 || pieceID == 8 || pieceID == 3 || pieceID == 4 || pieceID == 10 || pieceID == 11)
138                   gamePieces[pieceID].hasMoved = true;
139           }

141           public boolean validateMove(int[] current, int[] next, String color){            
142               
143               if (current == next){
144                   return false;
145               }
146               
147               int pieceID = board[current[0]][current[1]];
148               if (pieceID == 0)
149                   return false;
150               
151               ChessPiece myPiece = gamePieces[pieceID];
152               
153               if (myPiece.verify_move(board, current, next)){
154                   if(!doesMoveCauseCheck(current, next, color))
155                   {
156                       this.applyMove(current, next);                
157                       return true;
158                   }
159                   else
160                       return false;
161               }
162               
163               if (this.verifySpecialMove(current, next)){
164                   if(!doesMoveCauseCheck(current, next, color))
165                   {
166                       this.applyMove(current, next);                
167                       return true;
168                   }
169                   else
170                       return false;
171               }            
172               return false;
173           }
174           
175           // Applies the proposed move on a copy of the board array to examine if it results in a check for the friendly King
176           // Does not apply Castling moves, which do not pass 'verifySpecialMove' if they result in a check for the friendly King
177           private boolean doesMoveCauseCheck(int[] current, int[] next, String color){
178               
179               int[][] test_board = new int[8][8];
180               
181               //deep copy of board array            
182               for (int x = 0; x < board.length; x++)
183                   for (int y = 0; y < board[x].length; y++)
184                       test_board[x][y] = board[x][y];
185                                                     
186                                                     
187               int pieceID = test_board[current[0]][current[1]];
188               
189               // Special Move: En Passant
190               if (pieceID == 7 || pieceID == 14){
191                   if (current[1] != next[1] && test_board[next[0]][next[1]] == 0){
192                       test_board[current[0]][next[1]] = 0;
193                   }
194               }
195               
196               // Common for all moves
197               test_board[next[0]][next[1]] = pieceID;
198               test_board[current[0]][current[1]] = 0;
199               
200               if(color == "white")            
201                   return gamePieces[1].isThereCheck(test_board, WKingPos);
202               else
203                   return gamePieces[8].isThereCheck(test_board, BKingPos);    
204               
205           }

229           private boolean verifySpecialMove(int[] current, int[] next){
230               
231               int pieceID = board[current[0]][current[1]];
232               
233               // En Passant
234               if (pieceID == 7 || pieceID == 14){
235                   if (current[1] != next[1] && board[next[0]][next[1]] == 0){                    
236                       if (gamePieces[pieceID].validate_passant(board, current, next, lastMove))
237                           return true;                    
238                   }                
239               }            
240               //Castling
241               if ((pieceID == 1 || pieceID == 8 ) && Math.abs(current[1] - next[1]) == 2)
242               {
243                   if(check_castling(pieceID, next))
244                       return true;
245               }
246               return false;
247           }

249           private boolean check_castling(int pieceID, int[] next){
250               ChessPiece myKing = gamePieces[pieceID];
251               // White King, Queenside castling
252               if (pieceID == 1 && next[0] == 7 && next[1] == 2){
253                   if (myKing.hasMoved == false && gamePieces[3].hasMoved == false){
254                       if(board[7][1] == 0 && board[7][2] == 0 && board[7][3] == 0){
255                           int[] passThrough = new int[]{7,3};
256                           int[] dest = new int[]{7,2};
257                           if(!myKing.isThereCheck(board, WKingPos) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, passThrough) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, dest)){                            
258                               return true;
259                           }
260                       }
261                   }
262               }
263               // White King, Kingside castling
264               if (pieceID == 1 && next[0] == 7 && next[1] == 6){
265                   if (myKing.hasMoved == false && gamePieces[4].hasMoved == false){
266                       if(board[7][5] == 0 && board[7][6] == 0){
267                           int[] passThrough = new int[]{7,5};
268                           int[] dest = new int[]{7,6};
269                           if(!myKing.isThereCheck(board, WKingPos) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, passThrough) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, dest)){                            
270                               return true;
271                           }
272                       }
273                   }
274               }
275               // Black King, Queenside castling
276               if (pieceID == 8 && next[0] == 0 && next[1] == 2){
277                   if (myKing.hasMoved == false && gamePieces[10].hasMoved == false){
278                       if(board[0][1] == 0 && board[0][2] == 0 && board[0][3] == 0){
279                           int[] passThrough = new int[]{0,3};
280                           int[] dest = new int[]{0,2};
281                           if(!myKing.isThereCheck(board, WKingPos) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, passThrough) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, dest)){                            
282                               return true;
283                           }
284                       }
285                   }
286               }
287               // Black King, Kingside castling
288               if (pieceID == 8 && next[0] == 0 && next[1] == 6){
289                   if (myKing.hasMoved == false && gamePieces[11].hasMoved == false){
290                       if(board[0][5] == 0 && board[0][6] == 0){
291                           int[] passThrough = new int[]{0,5};
292                           int[] dest = new int[]{0,6};
293                           if(!myKing.isThereCheck(board, WKingPos) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, passThrough) && !myKing.isThereCheck(board, dest)){
294                               return true;
295                           }
296                       }
297                   }
298               }
299               return false;
300           }

304               int[] endPos = lastMove[1];

315           public Boolean decodeMove( String move ){        
316               
317               String[] tokens = move.split("[ ]");
318               int startRow = Integer.parseInt(tokens[0]);
319               int startCol = Integer.parseInt(tokens[1]);
320               int endRow = Integer.parseInt(tokens[2]);
321               int endCol = Integer.parseInt(tokens[3]);
322               
323               if(startRow == 1 & startCol == 1 & endRow == 1 & endCol == 1)
324                   return false;
325               else{
326                   int[] startPos = new int[]{startRow, startCol};
327                   int[] endPos = new int[]{endRow, endCol};            
328                   this.applyMove(startPos, endPos);
329                   
330                   lastMove[0] = startPos;
331                   lastMove[1] = endPos;                
332                   return true;
333               }
334           }
